  "prompt": "What's a safe investment plan for a 70 year old who just inherited $500,000 and needs none of it to live on?",
  "response": "For a 70-year-old with a $500,000 inheritance and no immediate need for the funds, a conservative, diversified investment strategy would be appropriate:\n\n1. Low-risk allocation:\n- 40-50% in high-quality bonds\n- 30-40% in blue-chip, dividend-paying stocks\n- 10-20% in cash or cash equivalents (money market, CDs)\n\n2. Specific recommendations:\n- Treasury bonds\n- Municipal bonds\n- Investment-grade corporate bonds\n- S&P 500 index funds\n- Large-cap dividend stocks\n- High-yield savings accounts\n- Certificates of Deposit (CDs)\n\n3. Considerations:\n- Prioritize capital preservation\n- Seek moderate, steady income\n- Minimize risk and volatility\n- Consider tax-efficient investments\n- Potentially consult a financial advisor\n\n4. Additional strategies:\n- Laddered bond strategy\n- Diversified ETFs\n- Some exposure to real estate investment trusts (REITs)\n\n5. Key goals:\n- Protect principal\n- Generate modest returns\n- Maintain liquidity\n- Minimize tax liability\n\nA personalized approach based on individual risk tolerance and specific financial goals is recommended.",
